  "texts": [
    "Most relevantly, Callahan et al [23] implemented a surveillance framework for hip implants, and Sanyal et al [25] implemented one for insulin pumps.",
    "To the best of our knowledge, however, our work is the first to apply a weakly supervised approach to consumer wearable surveillance.",
    "Without prescription records, consumer wearable surveillance can be challenging to scale.",
    "LimitationsWe acknowledge that the STARR data set is confined to a small health care system in a single geographic region, which is known [13] to serve populations with higher percentages of male, White, and older individuals.",
    "We recommend other institutions to monitor their patient population by developing their own surveillance framework using our weakly supervised methodology."
  ],
